desc: Demographics are characteristics of the population of the area. These include overall number of people living in the area, age and sex of the population, birth rates, and migration rates.
Environmental impact captures the effect of human activity on the environment and climate. This includes carbon emissions.
Health risk factors include health conditions and behavioral risk factors that can affect overall well-being.
The mortality domain includes measures of the rate at which people die as well as measures of life expectancy.
The physical and natural environment domain captures hazardous environmental exposures as well as features of built environments and natural environments.
The social, economic, and services environment are factors that influence the social and economic opportunities and access to health care available to residents.
